 way in both actively setting a large number of people in motion and passively entertaining and inspiring them. This volume presents the scientific discipline that in modern society has specialised in sociological observation and description of sport. The following topics are discussed: pioneers of sports sociology, phases of development, influences and driving forces, basic principles of sociology, sports of society, research levels and theories, possibilities and limits of application as well as dangers.Suitable as an introduction, but also for in-depth studies in sports sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMedicinexClinical MedicinexPublic Health. 4aEinführung. 4aGesellschaft. 4aKörper. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aSport. 4aSportwissenschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aBody.  aIntroduction.  aSociological Theory.  aSociology.  aSport Science.  aSport.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013z978311102523008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2000-2009z9783110463415oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Sozialw. 2000-2009z9783110463392oZDB-23-TSW0 cprintz978383761407740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839414071?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839414071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839414071/original  a978-3-11-102523-0  transcript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TSOc2000d2009  aZDB-23-TSWc2000d2009